                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5999: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Lambert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-25T16:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25, 1928—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Department’s telegram September 14, 4 p.m. Indications are that … has not
                    returned to Nicaragua. Foreign Office today informed me that he last Saturday
                    arrived at Las Juntas in southern Guanacaste with small theatrical troop and is
                    under surveillance.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Managua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">De Lambert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
